---
title: Logistikos — Payment lifecycle (authorize → capture → refund)
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant Customer
    participant Frontend as React Frontend
    participant Controller as PaymentMethods Controller
    participant Processor as Payments::Processor
    participant Adapter as Gateway Adapter
    participant Gateway as MockAdapter / Stripe
    participant DB as Database

    Note over Customer,DB: 1. Add payment method

    Customer->>Frontend: Enter card details
    Frontend->>Gateway: Tokenize via Stripe.js / MockAdapter
    Gateway-->>Frontend: gateway_token
    Frontend->>Controller: POST /payment_methods {token, last4, brand}
    Controller->>DB: INSERT PaymentMethod (encrypted token)

    Note over Customer,DB: 2. Authorize on order acceptance

    Controller->>Processor: authorize(order, payment_method)
    activate Processor
    Processor->>Processor: Generate idempotency_key
    Processor->>Adapter: authorize(amount, token, idempotency_key)
    Adapter->>Gateway: API call
    Gateway-->>Adapter: {authorization_id, status: ok}
    Adapter-->>Processor: Result
    Processor->>DB: INSERT Payment (status: authorized)
    deactivate Processor

    Note over Customer,DB: 3. Capture on delivery completion

    Controller->>Processor: capture(payment)
    activate Processor
    Processor->>DB: Check payment.status == authorized
    Processor->>Adapter: capture(authorization_id, idempotency_key)
    Adapter->>Gateway: API call
    Gateway-->>Adapter: {status: captured}
    Processor->>DB: UPDATE Payment (status: captured)
    Processor->>DB: INSERT DriverEarning
    Note right of DB: net = gross - platform_fee (15%)
    deactivate Processor

    Note over Customer,DB: 4. Refund on cancellation

    alt Before capture (void)
        Controller->>Processor: refund(payment)
        Processor->>Adapter: void(authorization_id)
        Adapter->>Gateway: Void authorization
        Processor->>DB: UPDATE Payment (status: voided)
    else After capture (refund)
        Controller->>Processor: refund(payment)
        Processor->>Adapter: refund(payment_id, amount)
        Adapter->>Gateway: Issue refund
        Processor->>DB: UPDATE Payment (status: refunded)
    end
